const vaultDescriptions:Record<string,string>={
 "Wall push-up":"Stand facing a wall with hands at chest height. Keep your body straight, bend your elbows toward the wall, then press away until arms are straight.",
 "Counter push-up":"Place hands on a stable counter or high bench. Walk feet back, keep ribs and hips in one line, lower your chest toward the edge, then press back up.",
 "Incline push-up":"Use a bench, table edge, or step for your hands. Keep the body long, lower with control, and push the surface away without letting hips sag.",
 "Slow negative push-up":"Start at the top of a push-up. Lower slowly for three to five counts, keeping elbows controlled, then reset if you cannot press back up cleanly.",
 "Pause push-up":"Lower toward the floor, pause briefly near the bottom while staying tight, then press back up. Use knees or an incline if the pause breaks your form.",
 "High plank hold":"Hold the top of a push-up with hands under shoulders. Brace your stomach, squeeze glutes lightly, and keep head, hips, and heels in one line.",
 "Knee plank":"Set elbows or hands under shoulders and keep knees on the mat. Make a straight line from shoulders to hips to knees while breathing steadily.",
 "Forearm plank":"Place elbows under shoulders, step feet back, and hold a long body line. Push the floor away gently and avoid dropping the hips.",
 "Long-lever plank":"Begin in forearm plank, then move elbows slightly forward. Keep the same straight body line; stop if the lower back starts to sag.",
 "Plank shoulder tap prep":"Hold a high plank with feet slightly wider than hips. Tap one shoulder with the opposite hand while keeping hips as still as possible.",
 "Bear crawl hold":"Start on hands and knees, tuck toes, then lift knees just above the floor. Keep back flat and breathe without rocking side to side.",
 "Sit-to-stand":"Sit near the front of a chair with feet flat. Lean slightly forward, stand tall without using hands, then sit back down slowly.",
 "Chair tap squat":"Stand in front of a chair. Push hips back until you lightly tap the chair, then stand up through your whole foot without collapsing knees inward.",
 "Bodyweight squat":"Stand with feet about hip to shoulder width. Sit hips back and down, keep chest tall, then stand by pressing through the floor.",
 "Tempo squat":"Perform a regular squat, but lower slowly for about three counts before standing. Keep knees tracking over toes the whole time.",
 "Squat pulse":"Lower into a comfortable squat and make small up-and-down pulses. Keep the movement short, controlled, and pain-free.",
 "Squat-to-reach":"Squat down with control, then stand and reach both arms overhead. Use the reach to open your chest and ribs, not to arch your lower back.",
 "Quiet high-knee march":"March in place without jumping. Lift one knee at a time, land softly, and keep your posture tall with relaxed shoulders.",
 "Glute bridge hold":"Lie on your back with knees bent and feet flat. Press through heels, lift hips, squeeze glutes, and hold without arching your lower back.",
 "Marching bridge":"Lift into a glute bridge, then raise one foot at a time like a slow march. Keep hips level instead of letting one side drop.",
 "Kickstand bridge":"Set one foot firmly and keep the other foot lightly touching the floor for balance. Lift hips using mostly the working leg.",
 "Single-leg bridge prep":"Lie on your back with one foot planted and the other knee lifted. Raise and lower hips while keeping your pelvis level.",
 "Supported calf raise":"Hold a wall or chair lightly. Rise onto the balls of both feet, pause at the top, then lower heels slowly.",
 "Slow eccentric calf raise":"Rise up onto your toes, then lower your heels slowly for three to five counts. Use support so the movement stays controlled.",
 "Single-leg calf prep":"Hold support and shift more weight into one foot. Rise and lower on that side with control, using the other foot only for balance if needed.",
 "Ankle rockers":"Stand or kneel with one foot planted. Gently move the knee forward over the toes while keeping the heel down, then return.",
 "Heel taps":"Lie on your back with knees bent up. Brace your core and slowly tap one heel to the floor at a time without your lower back lifting.",
 "Bent-knee brace":"Lie on your back with knees bent and feet up or planted. Tighten your midsection gently, breathe, and keep ribs from flaring.",
 "Dead bug":"Lie on your back with arms up and knees bent. Slowly reach opposite arm and leg away, then return while keeping your lower back heavy.",
 "Dead bug pause":"Move into a dead bug reach and hold for a short pause. Keep breathing and return before the lower back lifts.",
 "Long-lever dead bug":"Perform dead bug with longer arm and leg reaches. Move slowly and shorten the reach if your back loses contact with the floor.",
 "Tucked hollow hold":"Lie on your back, tuck knees toward chest, and lift shoulders slightly. Press lower back into the floor and hold a compact hollow shape.",
 "Short side plank":"Lie on one side with knees bent and elbow under shoulder. Lift hips so shoulders, hips, and knees form a straight line.",
 "Side plank hold":"Stack elbow under shoulder and lift hips into a long side line. Keep the underside waist active and avoid rolling forward or backward.",
 "Side plank reach":"Hold side plank and reach the top arm overhead or forward. Keep hips lifted and move the arm without collapsing the waist.",
 "Side plank rotation prep":"Start in side plank and slowly rotate the top shoulder slightly toward the floor, then open again. Keep the motion small and controlled.",
 "Three-point hold":"Start on hands and knees, then lift one hand or one knee slightly so only three points touch the floor. Stay square and steady.",
 "Bird dog":"From hands and knees, reach one arm and the opposite leg long. Keep hips level and return slowly before switching sides.",
 "Bird dog crunch":"Reach into bird dog, then draw elbow and opposite knee toward each other under your body. Round slightly, then extend again with control.",
 "Bird dog hover":"Set up like bird dog and add a small knee hover if possible. Keep the back flat and make the movement slow rather than high.",
 "Quadruped brace":"Start on hands and knees with wrists under shoulders and knees under hips. Brace your stomach as if preparing to lift the knees, but stay controlled.",
 "Recovery reset flow":"Move slowly through gentle positions like bridge breathing, quadruped reach, and easy squat. The goal is relaxed control, not intensity.",
 "Bridge breathing":"Hold a glute bridge and take slow breaths. Keep ribs down, glutes lightly active, and hips steady.",
 "Mobility squat flow":"Move through an easy squat with a reach or small rotation. Stay within a comfortable range and use it to loosen hips and ankles.",
 "Calisthenics skill flow":"Practice clean bodyweight shapes such as plank, push-up setup, and tuck hold. Move slowly and prioritize control over difficulty.",
 "L-sit tuck prep":"Sit between blocks or sturdy supports, press arms straight, tuck knees, and try to lightly lift hips or feet while keeping shoulders down.",
 "Crow-prep balance":"Place hands on the floor, bend elbows slightly, and bring knees toward upper arms. Shift weight forward carefully, keeping toes close to the floor.",
 "Quiet conditioning circuit":"Cycle through low-impact moves such as marching, squat reach, and plank holds. Keep feet quiet and breathing steady.",
 "Balance reset":"Stand tall on one leg or shift weight slowly side to side. Use a wall if needed and keep the movement smooth and controlled.",
 "Posture builder":"Use bird-dog style reaches and gentle chest opening. Keep your spine long and move from the upper back rather than shrugging shoulders.",
 "Skill prep flow":"Move through simple plank, push-up, and core shapes. Treat each position like practice for future calisthenics skills."
};
function vaultDescription(item:{name:string},move:Move){return vaultDescriptions[item.name]||move.detail}
